k performed by residents, relatives, volunteers and staff in nursing homes. It demonstrates how boundaries between paid and unpaid work are flexible, varying considerably with conditions, time, place and intersectional populations. By examining the complex labour process within nursing homes, this book provides insight and understanding which will be critical in planning for nursing home care post-pandemic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNursing homes. 0aUnpaid labor. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aArmstrong, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArmstrong, Pat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArmstrong, Pat, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBraedley, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoiniere, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobsen, Frode F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlostermann, Janna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLowndes, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSortland, Oddrunn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStreeter, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStruthers, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzebehely, Marta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUlmanen, Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÅgotnes, Gudmund, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08